main event: A circular object, the size of a garbage can, was observed approaching from the east, circling in a tight radius for approximately 6 minutes before departing in a southerly direction while gaining altitude.
interesting points: The object circled for 6 minutes before gaining altitude and departing south., The sighting was conducted under clear weather conditions., The observer was a civilian housewife with normal reliability., The object was described as reddish and circular in shape., There is a suspicion that the sighting may have been related to a missile launch from Cape Canaveral.
sighted object: circular object, size of a garbage can
